title: Adeline Mowbray
creator: Amelia Opie
description:
LibriVox recording of Adeline Mowbray, by Amelia Opie. Read by P Moscato.

Everybody makes mistakes, and everything has a price. This novel describes, according to its name, the life of Adeline Mowbray, full of everything: sorrow, happiness, falsehood, truth, kindness, and mistakes. This novel is an exploration of the human heart. Be prepared for a strong and enjoyable read. (Summary by Stav Nisser)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B Part 1 (199MB) Download M4B Part 2 (98MB)
